This project is a local-first web application for:

* importing .xlsx files
* parsing and normalizing article/product data
* storing normalized records in a local database
* building a fast and accurate article search index
* exposing the functionality through a local web UI

Default architectural priorities:

1. Exact and prefix article search are more important than generic full-text search.

2. Keep both original and normalized article values.

3. Prefer deterministic normalization and deduplication.

4. Prefer SQLite or another local embedded database unless the repo already uses something else.

5. UI must support local file upload, import feedback, search, filters, and result details.

6. All code changes must preserve local-first development and simple setup.

7. For any library/framework setup or version-specific code generation, use Context7 when available.

8. For complex architecture decomposition or ambiguous implementation tradeoffs, use Sequential Thinking when available.
